LAFIA – The passing of Alhaji Isa Mustapher Agwai, the emir of Lafia, has been announced. He died  on Thursday at the age of 80. Malam Suleiman Abubakar Ajiyan Lafia, who confirmed the death, said the emir died in Mizamir private teaching hospital, Abuja, after a protracted illness. Alhaji Isa Agwai was on the throne as the emir of Lafia for 40 years.  He was the chairman Nasarawa State Council of Chiefs. Alhaji Suleiman disclosed that the family would announce details of the burial arrangements later.